sequenceDiagram
    actor App as Your App<br/>(korTTY)
    participant FE as MoshTerminal<br/>Frontend
    participant CS as MoshClient<br/>Session
    participant UDP as UDP Network
    participant SRV as mosh-server<br/>(C++)

    Note over App,SRV: Phase 1 — Bootstrap & Session Setup
    App->>CS: new MoshClientSession(addr, key, 80, 24)
    App->>FE: new MoshTerminalFrontend(session)

    Note over App,SRV: Phase 2 — Initial Wake-Up
    App->>FE: sendInitialWakeUp()
    FE->>CS: sendUserInput([0x00])
    CS->>UDP: AES-128-OCB encrypted datagram
    UDP->>SRV: encrypted datagram

    Note over App,SRV: Phase 3 — Start Background Thread
    App->>FE: start()
    activate FE
    Note right of FE: Background receive<br/>thread (daemon) starts

    Note over App,SRV: Phase 4 — Active Session Loop
    SRV-->>UDP: host output (terminal data)
    UDP-->>CS: encrypted datagram
    CS->>CS: decrypt → defragment<br/>→ protobuf parse → framebuffer
    CS-->>FE: framebuffer updated
    FE-->>App: takeRenderedOutput() → ANSI frame
    App->>FE: sendUserInput(keystrokes)
    FE->>CS: sendUserInput(bytes)
    CS->>UDP: AES-128-OCB encrypted datagram
    UDP->>SRV: encrypted datagram

    Note over App,SRV: Phase 5 — Resize
    App->>FE: sendResize(cols, rows)
    FE->>CS: sendResize(cols, rows)
    CS->>UDP: resize datagram
    UDP->>SRV: resize notification

    Note over App,SRV: Phase 6 — Shutdown
    App->>FE: close()
    deactivate FE
    FE->>CS: close()
    Note right of CS: UDP socket closed
